---
description: Architecture rules for the Git desktop client
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

This project uses a modular monolith architecture.

Architecture layers:
- Presentation layer: React UI, screens, components, view state
- Application layer: use-case orchestration
- Domain layer: core models and business rules
- Infrastructure layer: Git CLI, filesystem, storage, AI providers, OS integrations

Mandatory boundaries:
- UI must not call Git directly.
- UI must not contain business rules for repository operations.
- Rust handles Git execution, filesystem access, OS interaction, and sensitive operations.
- AI provider access must be abstracted behind a service interface.
- Git provider access must be abstracted behind a service interface.
- Domain models must stay framework-agnostic where possible.

Frontend rules:
- put feature code under feature modules
- keep reusable UI primitives separate from feature components
- use TanStack Query for command/query data
- use Zustand only for UI/session state
- do not store server-like data in Zustand if Query is more appropriate

Rust rules:
- command handlers must be thin
- parsing Git output belongs in infrastructure/parsers
- external process execution must be isolated behind executor abstractions
- raw stderr must not be the only error contract
- map external failures to typed app errors

Change policy:
- if a request crosses layers, preserve boundaries
- do not shortcut architecture for convenience
- if a shortcut seems necessary, explain it explicitly before applying it